WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.005 --> 00:00:06.528
Run.

2
00:00:06.570 --> 00:00:07.614
Josh!

3
00:00:07.656 --> 00:00:09.136
Mom!

4
00:00:14.997 --> 00:00:16.781
This place doesn't seem real.
does it?

5
00:00:17.910 --> 00:00:19.085
Mom!

6
00:00:19.127 --> 00:00:20.302
When we fell
through that sinkhole.

7
00:00:20.343 --> 00:00:22.563
we ended up some time
around 10.000 B.C.

8
00:00:22.601 --> 00:00:24.429
We all have people
we want to get back to.

9
00:00:24.468 --> 00:00:26.165
We're not gonna give up.
We're gonna find a way home.

10
00:00:27.640 --> 00:00:30.251
I have these flashes.

11
00:00:30.292 --> 00:00:31.771
Your Mom and Josh
are in the past.

12
00:00:31.813 --> 00:00:33.989
How is that possible?

13
00:00:34.029 --> 00:00:35.595
We're going down there. Gavin.

14
00:00:35.637 --> 00:00:37.247
and you're gonna help us do it.

15
00:00:37.285 --> 00:00:38.764
Aldridge jumped!

16
00:00:38.807 --> 00:00:40.330
We need to stick together.

17
00:00:40.371 --> 00:00:41.981
There's safety in numbers.

18
00:00:42.021 --> 00:00:43.936
I can't leave you here.

19
00:00:43.977 --> 00:00:46.023
Mom. no.

20
00:00:46.845 --> 00:00:48.456
- Levi?
- Eve.

21
00:00:48.495 --> 00:00:50.976
Gavin knows about us.
He asked me if I loved you.

22
00:00:51.015 --> 00:00:51.885
I didn't have to say anything.

23
00:00:53.317 --> 00:00:54.449
That's a hunting trap.

24
00:00:54.490 --> 00:00:57.189
Somebody made that.
We're not alone.

25
00:00:57.228 --> 00:00:58.621
My grandfather told me
about you.

26
00:00:58.662 --> 00:01:01.013
The boy is
not who you think he is.

27
00:01:01.052 --> 00:01:04.403
Isiah is Gavin
and he needs your help.

28
00:01:04.440 --> 00:01:08.139
There is a portal
and it leads to 1988.

29
00:01:08.178 --> 00:01:10.180
You have to get him through it.

30
00:01:10.219 --> 00:01:11.873
- I can't let you do this.
- Silas!

31
00:01:14.736 --> 00:01:15.912
Josh?

32
00:01:15.953 --> 00:01:17.694
There's somewhere I need to go.

33
00:01:17.734 --> 00:01:19.432
That's impossible.

34
00:01:19.473 --> 00:01:21.432
There's more you need to see.

35
00:01:21.471 --> 00:01:23.821
This might be our only chance
to get Mom and Josh back.

36
00:01:23.861 --> 00:01:26.037
There's gonna be a sinkhole
in Seattle.

37
00:01:29.987 --> 00:01:32.250
I think we made it.

38
00:01:32.289 --> 00:01:34.117
Let's go find Mom and Josh.

39
00:01:50.322 --> 00:01:51.932
Smile.

40
00:01:53.491 --> 00:01:56.102
A beautiful day. isn't it?

41
00:01:56.142 --> 00:01:57.926
I'd like it better
if it wasn't so hot.

42
00:01:57.967 --> 00:01:59.229
I'm burning up.

43
00:02:02.965 --> 00:02:04.880
Can I go for a walk with Doc?

44
00:02:04.917 --> 00:02:06.919
Yes. but don't go too far.

45
00:02:08.176 --> 00:02:09.525
Come on. Doc.

46
00:02:10.609 --> 00:02:12.307
Come on. Doc.

47
00:02:14.521 --> 00:02:16.436
What's going on. Doc?

48
00:02:16.474 --> 00:02:17.518
Doc!

49
00:02:20.603 --> 00:02:23.084
Doc.

50
00:02:51.754 --> 00:02:53.104
- Carly.
- Carly.

51
00:03:16.388 --> 00:03:17.650
Carly. move!

52
00:03:22.993 --> 00:03:25.647
Carly. no!

53
00:03:34.939 --> 00:03:38.073
Carly. Carly.

54
00:03:38.112 --> 00:03:39.461
Carly!
- Oh. baby! Are you hurt?

55
00:03:39.503 --> 00:03:41.853
- You okay?
- I'm fine. Where's Doc?

56
00:03:43.892 --> 00:03:47.504
Oh. my God. oh. my God.

57
00:04:24.947 --> 00:04:26.905
- Morning.
- Hey.

58
00:04:26.947 --> 00:04:29.210
- Any progress last night?
- No.

59
00:04:29.249 --> 00:04:31.904
Silas still isn't talking.
- He will.

60
00:04:31.944 --> 00:04:33.206
It's been 24 hours.

61
00:04:33.247 --> 00:04:34.640
If he was gonna talk.
he would've talked.

62
00:04:34.679 --> 00:04:36.159
Well. he has to.

63
00:04:36.199 --> 00:04:39.245
Aldridge said Silas. he helped
create these sinkholes.

64
00:04:39.285 --> 00:04:41.722
If anyone knows how to get Josh
and Riley back from 1988.

65
00:04:41.762 --> 00:04:43.415
it's him.
- Yeah.

66
00:04:43.457 --> 00:04:45.851
Well. Marybeth and Lucas.
any word on them?

67
00:04:45.890 --> 00:04:47.196
No.

68
00:04:47.235 --> 00:04:48.715
No one's been able to find them.

69
00:04:48.755 --> 00:04:50.539
With Marybeth's injuries.
I'm getting really concerned.

70
00:04:50.581 --> 00:04:52.975
Yeah. and then there's
Aldridge and there's Scott.

71
00:04:53.015 --> 00:04:54.581
and Veronica...
They're all missing.

72
00:04:54.622 --> 00:04:57.364
So it's just... at least when
Josh was here. I had somebody.

73
00:04:57.403 --> 00:05:00.450
Now I'm all alone.

74
00:05:00.486 --> 00:05:02.662
You're not alone. Eve.

75
00:05:02.702 --> 00:05:04.138
I happen to be
excellent company.

76
00:05:04.180 --> 00:05:07.879
Yes. Yes. you are.

77
00:05:07.917 --> 00:05:10.963
Look. you have faced
so much adversity before.

78
00:05:11.003 --> 00:05:13.396
Everything you went through
with Gavin.

79
00:05:13.434 --> 00:05:17.046
Izzy's accident.
you got through that.

80
00:05:17.085 --> 00:05:18.477
We will get through this.

81
00:05:21.211 --> 00:05:22.604
Yeah.

82
00:05:26.337 --> 00:05:28.382
You don't look so good. Silas.

83
00:05:28.424 --> 00:05:30.034
Let me guess.

84
00:05:30.074 --> 00:05:33.033
Your joints are starting to
hurt. you can't think straight.

85
00:05:33.073 --> 00:05:34.857
Probably have a headache too.

86
00:05:34.897 --> 00:05:38.248
That's what happens when you
don't drink water for 24 hours.

87
00:05:38.285 --> 00:05:43.029
Why was it so important
to keep Isiah here?

88
00:05:43.066 --> 00:05:45.938
You don't want to tell us
what's really going on. Fine.

89
00:05:45.977 --> 00:05:48.544
But you will tell me
how to get my daughter back.

90
00:05:51.711 --> 00:05:53.016
Take a sip.

91
00:05:53.058 --> 00:05:54.755
And then you're going
to start talking.

92
00:06:00.227 --> 00:06:01.445
Sam. hey!

93
00:06:03.354 --> 00:06:04.704
I'm not thirsty.

94
00:06:10.785 --> 00:06:11.786
We have to find another tactic.

95
00:06:11.827 --> 00:06:13.263
'cause that one's not working.

96
00:06:13.305 --> 00:06:14.654
He'll break.

97
00:06:14.695 --> 00:06:17.219
At some point.
we have to be humane.

98
00:06:17.258 --> 00:06:19.347
He's our only hope of getting
Josh and Riley back.

99
00:06:19.386 --> 00:06:21.867
We cannot let him die.

100
00:06:21.906 --> 00:06:24.430
What's going on. Sam?

101
00:06:24.471 --> 00:06:25.907
I'm fine. Levi.

102
00:06:28.074 --> 00:06:30.729
Look. I don't pretend to know
what you're going through.

103
00:06:30.770 --> 00:06:32.336
I just don't want you doing
something you're gonna regret.

104
00:06:32.378 --> 00:06:33.901
The only thing I'll regret
is if I don't

105
00:06:33.941 --> 00:06:37.379
do everything in my power
to bring Riley back.

106
00:06:37.417 --> 00:06:39.289
I'm not saying we give up.

107
00:06:39.328 --> 00:06:41.591
but she's a hell
of a lot safer back in 1988.

108
00:06:41.631 --> 00:06:44.939
I still plan on finding a way
home to where we belong.

109
00:06:44.976 --> 00:06:46.717
and I'm not doing that
without my daughter.

110
00:06:46.759 --> 00:06:49.326
Hey. what's going on?

111
00:06:52.058 --> 00:06:55.148
Silas is stubborn.
but eventually. he'll talk.

112
00:06:55.187 --> 00:06:57.450
I'm just afraid we're gonna
run out of time before he does.

113
00:06:57.488 --> 00:07:00.448
Paara convinced her people
to allow us to question Silas.

114
00:07:00.487 --> 00:07:01.706
but they're expecting him back.

115
00:07:01.748 --> 00:07:03.010
They're gonna be here
this afternoon.

116
00:07:03.051 --> 00:07:04.270
They're just gonna have to wait.

117
00:07:04.311 --> 00:07:06.313
I don't know how patient
they're gonna be.

118
00:07:06.352 --> 00:07:08.310
Look. Silas lied about
his identity.

119
00:07:08.351 --> 00:07:09.961
People are dead
because of his actions.

120
00:07:10.002 --> 00:07:11.307
They want to
hold him accountable.

121
00:07:11.349 --> 00:07:12.655
That's not my problem.

122
00:07:12.696 --> 00:07:14.306
Actually. it's all our problem.

123
00:07:14.347 --> 00:07:16.697
Paara's people are supposed to
bring us food today.

124
00:07:16.738 --> 00:07:18.130
I don't think we want
to make enemies

125
00:07:18.169 --> 00:07:20.388
of the people
who are trying to help.

126
00:07:20.429 --> 00:07:22.300
We need to survive here
on a long-term basis. Sam.

127
00:07:22.342 --> 00:07:23.473
The best way to do that

128
00:07:23.515 --> 00:07:25.082
is with help from Paara
and her village.

129
00:07:25.121 --> 00:07:27.254
Then you talk to her. Ty.
Tell her we need an extension.

130
00:07:27.295 --> 00:07:28.732
She's a good person.
She'll listen to you.

131
00:07:32.029 --> 00:07:34.815
- I can try.
- Do whatever you want.

132
00:07:34.854 --> 00:07:36.595
Silas isn't going anywhere
until he talks.

133
00:07:36.635 --> 00:07:37.679
Sam.

134
00:07:39.808 --> 00:07:41.679
We're gonna get Silas to talk.

135
00:07:41.720 --> 00:07:43.939
I don't care
what we have to do. Levi.

136
00:07:43.976 --> 00:07:47.370
I just want my family back.

137
00:07:52.407 --> 00:07:55.932
- I really hate this place.
- I'm sorry.

138
00:07:55.968 --> 00:07:57.622
I shouldn't
have brought you here.

139
00:07:57.663 --> 00:07:59.883
You didn't.
It was my choice to jump.

140
00:07:59.922 --> 00:08:01.576
I want to get to Mom and Josh
just as much as you.

141
00:08:01.618 --> 00:08:02.967
I know you do.

142
00:08:03.007 --> 00:08:05.488
Look. the deal was
when we landed in Seattle.

143
00:08:05.527 --> 00:08:07.268
we said we'd walk
20 miles a day.

144
00:08:07.308 --> 00:08:09.440
Okay. we're never gonna
get to LA at this rate.

145
00:08:13.043 --> 00:08:15.480
Have you had a vision of them?
Mom and Josh?

146
00:08:15.520 --> 00:08:17.348
No.
We've been here a while

147
00:08:17.390 --> 00:08:18.609
and I haven't had one
the whole time.

148
00:08:18.650 --> 00:08:19.738
Why not?

149
00:08:19.778 --> 00:08:20.909
I think the visions
were memories

150
00:08:20.951 --> 00:08:23.867
from my childhood
when I was Isiah.

151
00:08:23.904 --> 00:08:25.210
Once I went through the light
they stopped.

152
00:08:25.251 --> 00:08:26.992
'cause I'm not a kid
down here anymore.

153
00:08:27.034 --> 00:08:29.906
- What about you. Ella?
- Same.

154
00:08:29.946 --> 00:08:33.166
Everything I saw
was from I was Lilly.

155
00:08:33.203 --> 00:08:36.641
The last vision was
right before we came down here.

156
00:08:36.678 --> 00:08:39.681
My sister. Veronica.
was in trouble.

157
00:08:39.720 --> 00:08:41.853
Now. I can't
even see her anymore.

158
00:08:41.893 --> 00:08:43.721
I have no idea if she's okay.

159
00:08:43.762 --> 00:08:46.721
What's that?

160
00:09:04.659 --> 00:09:06.748
I need a break.
- We just took a break.

161
00:09:10.653 --> 00:09:12.306
Maybe we'd have a better
chance to make it

162
00:09:12.348 --> 00:09:13.958
if we'd been prepared.

163
00:09:13.999 --> 00:09:17.306
We don't have food. supplies.
We don't even have a compass.

164
00:09:17.346 --> 00:09:19.609
Yeah. well.
no one asked you to come.

165
00:09:19.648 --> 00:09:22.520
Hey. easy. Okay?
I know we're on edge.

166
00:09:22.559 --> 00:09:25.823
We're not gonna make it
unless we work together. okay?

167
00:09:25.860 --> 00:09:27.819
We're not gonna make it
if we starve either.

168
00:09:27.858 --> 00:09:30.208
Yeah. good point.

169
00:09:30.248 --> 00:09:32.598
Okay. wait here.

170
00:09:32.640 --> 00:09:34.511
Where are you going?

171
00:09:34.550 --> 00:09:37.030
I'm gonna get us some lunch.

172
00:10:34.595 --> 00:10:35.770
Okay.

173
00:10:37.937 --> 00:10:39.634
Easy.

174
00:10:39.677 --> 00:10:42.549
I'm just... we're all friends.

175
00:10:42.588 --> 00:10:45.025
Easy.

176
00:10:45.064 --> 00:10:46.196
Okay.

177
00:11:29.466 --> 00:11:31.685
- You okay?
- I think so.

178
00:11:38.592 --> 00:11:40.812
Where are Lilly and Isiah?

179
00:11:40.849 --> 00:11:42.721
I have no idea.

180
00:11:49.757 --> 00:11:51.933
Are we in 1988?

181
00:11:51.973 --> 00:11:53.104
I mean. we went into that light.

182
00:11:53.145 --> 00:11:54.625
so I guess we should be.

183
00:12:08.003 --> 00:12:09.396
It's more like the '50s to me.

184
00:12:23.863 --> 00:12:27.301
This is definitely 1988.

185
00:12:40.112 --> 00:12:41.896
There they are.
We have to stop them.

186
00:12:41.936 --> 00:12:44.460
No. wait. Riley. stop!
Wait. they're gonna be okay.

187
00:12:44.499 --> 00:12:47.937
- How do you know that?
- Because I'm okay.

188
00:12:47.974 --> 00:12:49.367
Isiah gets adopted.

189
00:12:49.410 --> 00:12:50.759
He's gonna grow up
and meet my mom

190
00:12:50.799 --> 00:12:53.715
and they're gonna have
me and Izzy.

191
00:12:53.755 --> 00:12:55.017
We can't get in the way.

192
00:12:57.577 --> 00:13:00.710
Okay. and what about Lilly?

193
00:13:00.749 --> 00:13:02.925
She said she had to find Isiah.

194
00:13:02.964 --> 00:13:05.271
so this must be her path too.

195
00:13:10.132 --> 00:13:12.047
What about us?

196
00:13:14.565 --> 00:13:15.696
How am I gonna
get back to my dad?

197
00:13:15.738 --> 00:13:17.609
How are you gonna
get back to your mom?

198
00:13:17.651 --> 00:13:18.826
The La Brea sinkhole's
not gonna open

199
00:13:18.867 --> 00:13:20.129
for another 30 years.

200
00:13:23.558 --> 00:13:27.039
Josh. I think we're stuck here.

201
00:13:37.505 --> 00:13:41.988
Look who's finally awake.
How you feeling?

202
00:13:42.022 --> 00:13:44.111
Much better this morning.
actually.

203
00:13:44.153 --> 00:13:45.633
Oh. yeah?

204
00:13:45.671 --> 00:13:48.108
Because for someone who
was just stabbed recently.

205
00:13:48.148 --> 00:13:51.020
I'd say you're doing very well.

206
00:13:51.060 --> 00:13:54.193
I suppose I'm a quick healer.

207
00:13:54.232 --> 00:13:56.669
Why did Silas stab you?

208
00:13:56.709 --> 00:13:58.406
I told you.

209
00:13:58.445 --> 00:14:01.404
He didn't want me to
take Isiah through the light.

210
00:14:01.444 --> 00:14:04.925
It is like you are allergic
to telling the truth.

211
00:14:04.963 --> 00:14:06.486
We've been here for 24 hours.

212
00:14:06.528 --> 00:14:09.487
camped outside a futuristic
building that you built.

213
00:14:09.526 --> 00:14:11.092
You've been
promising me answers.

214
00:14:11.131 --> 00:14:12.611
but all I've got
are more questions.

215
00:14:12.652 --> 00:14:15.220
Well. you should be happy
because I finally have

216
00:14:15.260 --> 00:14:17.350
the strength I'll need
to make it to the building.

217
00:14:17.389 --> 00:14:19.957
Great. Fantastic.
Let's go.

218
00:14:19.995 --> 00:14:21.388
Scott. hang on.

219
00:14:21.431 --> 00:14:23.215
There are some things
I need to tell you first.

220
00:14:23.252 --> 00:14:24.689
Yeah. I bet.

221
00:14:24.730 --> 00:14:26.428
The people in that building
want me dead.

222
00:14:26.469 --> 00:14:28.950
If I step inside.
they'll kill me.

223
00:14:28.989 --> 00:14:32.689
And by extension. you.

224
00:14:32.726 --> 00:14:34.293
You should've
told me that before.

225
00:14:34.334 --> 00:14:36.292
Then you wouldn't have
stuck around for so long.

226
00:14:36.332 --> 00:14:37.898
Yeah. you're damn right.

227
00:14:37.939 --> 00:14:41.595
Scott. if we don't make it
into that building soon.

228
00:14:41.632 --> 00:14:44.809
very bad things
are gonna happen.

229
00:14:44.848 --> 00:14:47.851
Everyone you care about
where you're from.

230
00:14:47.887 --> 00:14:51.282
all of your friends
down here in the clearing.

231
00:14:51.321 --> 00:14:54.541
they will die unless
I get inside that building.

232
00:14:57.317 --> 00:14:59.101
Prove it.

233
00:14:59.142 --> 00:15:00.753
Isn't the fact that
I've shown you a building

234
00:15:00.791 --> 00:15:02.706
in 10.000 B.C. proof enough?

235
00:15:04.572 --> 00:15:06.661
- That's a fair point.
- If you want to save

236
00:15:06.702 --> 00:15:10.750
the people you love
then you'll help me.

237
00:15:10.785 --> 00:15:15.573
You know. I really dislike
you sometimes. Aldridge.

238
00:15:15.608 --> 00:15:18.132
But. yeah. I'm in.

239
00:15:28.380 --> 00:15:31.383
On your feet.

240
00:15:31.423 --> 00:15:33.295
Move.

241
00:15:33.333 --> 00:15:35.117
I'm giving you one last chance.

242
00:15:39.111 --> 00:15:41.200
Sam. put the gun down!

243
00:15:41.241 --> 00:15:44.505
Tell me how
to bring my daughter back.

244
00:15:44.543 --> 00:15:46.588
- This isn't who you are.
- Sam.

245
00:15:49.758 --> 00:15:52.848
Truth is I can't
bring your daughter back.

246
00:15:52.885 --> 00:15:56.149
But there's someone who can.

247
00:15:56.186 --> 00:15:58.754
Rebecca Aldridge.
- Aldridge is missing.

248
00:15:58.794 --> 00:16:01.318
I can help you find her.

249
00:16:01.358 --> 00:16:04.622
There's a place in the woods.
Day's journey due north.

250
00:16:04.658 --> 00:16:07.835
What kind of place?
We need details.

251
00:16:07.874 --> 00:16:11.007
Building
made of glass and steel.

252
00:16:11.046 --> 00:16:14.571
It's 30 stories high.
You won't miss it.

253
00:16:14.609 --> 00:16:16.088
I have to warn you.

254
00:16:16.128 --> 00:16:18.565
there are dangers there
you will not be prepared for.

255
00:16:18.605 --> 00:16:21.129
A building of glass and steel
in 10.000 B.C.?

256
00:16:21.168 --> 00:16:23.127
You're serious?
- Turn around.

257
00:16:25.079 --> 00:16:27.299
I am.

258
00:16:27.339 --> 00:16:31.647
Your only chance to save your
children is to find Rebecca.

259
00:16:31.683 --> 00:16:33.902
That glass building
is where she's headed.

260
00:16:37.853 --> 00:16:40.029
- Okay. that was a lot.
- Yeah.

261
00:16:40.069 --> 00:16:41.549
What are we thinking?

262
00:16:41.589 --> 00:16:42.807
I'm gonna go find Aldridge
and that building.

263
00:16:42.849 --> 00:16:44.067
I'm going with you.

264
00:16:44.109 --> 00:16:45.241
You can't be serious.
Silas we lying.

265
00:16:45.282 --> 00:16:46.849
You don't know that.

266
00:16:46.889 --> 00:16:48.848
You just pulled a gun on a
man and threatened to kill him.

267
00:16:48.888 --> 00:16:51.021
You think that's how you get
people to tell the truth?

268
00:16:51.061 --> 00:16:52.976
All I know is
we have a lead now.

269
00:16:53.015 --> 00:16:54.625
We need to check it out.

270
00:16:54.666 --> 00:16:55.710
Has it occurred to anyone

271
00:16:55.753 --> 00:16:57.276
that this is
Silas' plan of escape?

272
00:16:57.317 --> 00:16:59.841
Get us all on some fool's
errand while he buggers off?

273
00:17:02.922 --> 00:17:06.708
Then we...
We keep him locked up.

274
00:17:06.744 --> 00:17:08.224
I'll stay with him.

275
00:17:08.265 --> 00:17:10.441
Levi. you two go verify
what he said.

276
00:17:10.482 --> 00:17:12.614
I'll make sure he doesn't leave
the truck until you get back.

277
00:17:12.653 --> 00:17:14.394
Good luck and hurry back.

278
00:17:17.172 --> 00:17:18.956
We shouldn't leave
Sam alone with Silas.

279
00:17:18.995 --> 00:17:20.431
He's not okay.

280
00:17:20.474 --> 00:17:22.867
I'll watch him.
Be safe out there. okay?

281
00:17:24.004 --> 00:17:25.875
Thank you.

282
00:17:25.910 --> 00:17:27.607
Ready?

283
00:17:34.264 --> 00:17:35.744
Okay.

284
00:17:38.361 --> 00:17:39.362
Eat as much as you can.

285
00:17:39.408 --> 00:17:40.539
We should get moving soon.

286
00:17:40.585 --> 00:17:42.891
Mm.
I'm gonna go get some water.

287
00:17:42.936 --> 00:17:45.025
I'll be right back.

288
00:17:45.074 --> 00:17:50.776
Listen. I'm sorry about before.

289
00:17:50.826 --> 00:17:53.133
I shouldn't have snapped
at you guys.

290
00:17:53.181 --> 00:17:56.097
Don't worry about it.
You got a lot on your mind.

291
00:18:01.113 --> 00:18:03.725
I made a huge mistake
coming down here.

292
00:18:08.522 --> 00:18:10.306
Why did you come down here?

293
00:18:13.839 --> 00:18:16.624
When I as a little girl.

294
00:18:16.673 --> 00:18:19.240
I was kidnapped.

295
00:18:19.288 --> 00:18:20.768
So was Veronica.

296
00:18:22.905 --> 00:18:25.473
And the only reason
I got through it

297
00:18:25.520 --> 00:18:29.175
was because of Veronica.

298
00:18:29.226 --> 00:18:32.534
Well. sounds like you were
lucky to have her.

299
00:18:32.581 --> 00:18:35.410
She looked out for me.

300
00:18:35.458 --> 00:18:37.983
protected me.

301
00:18:38.031 --> 00:18:39.293
We're not related.

302
00:18:39.337 --> 00:18:43.341
but she basically
became my sister.

303
00:18:43.392 --> 00:18:46.047
So when I saw that vision
of her in danger.

304
00:18:46.093 --> 00:18:49.444
I wanted to get
down here to help.

305
00:18:49.492 --> 00:18:52.844
but now. I can't see her.

306
00:18:52.893 --> 00:18:57.594
Look. I don't know
how I'm going to find her.

307
00:18:57.644 --> 00:19:01.605
For all I know. she's dead
and coming here was a waste.

308
00:19:03.834 --> 00:19:08.186
Oh. God. I'm... I'm so scared.

309
00:19:08.237 --> 00:19:11.806
And I don't know if I'm strong
enough to make it down here.

310
00:19:11.853 --> 00:19:13.333
Okay.

311
00:19:16.736 --> 00:19:19.956
Remember...

312
00:19:20.006 --> 00:19:23.183
remember when I met you
when we were kids?

313
00:19:23.229 --> 00:19:25.318
When you were called Lilly?

314
00:19:25.364 --> 00:19:27.061
And I came in at the clearing

315
00:19:27.109 --> 00:19:31.069
and I hurt my wrist
and you help bandage me up?

316
00:19:32.950 --> 00:19:36.605
You were so sure of yourself.

317
00:19:36.653 --> 00:19:40.701
You were so brave.

318
00:19:40.752 --> 00:19:43.712
Deep down. that's who you are.

319
00:19:43.759 --> 00:19:45.369
You just need to remember that.

320
00:19:47.378 --> 00:19:51.034
That's nice of you to say...

321
00:19:51.082 --> 00:19:53.737
but I'm not that kid anymore.

322
00:20:29.089 --> 00:20:33.615
Oh. God.

323
00:20:33.666 --> 00:20:34.885
- Hey.
- Hey.

324
00:20:34.931 --> 00:20:36.889
We're ready to go.
Everything all right?

325
00:20:36.935 --> 00:20:39.198
- Yeah. Yeah. I'm good.
- Okay.

326
00:20:42.644 --> 00:20:44.254
All right. let's go.

327
00:20:51.492 --> 00:20:54.799
Sam.

328
00:20:54.849 --> 00:20:57.721
Some water?
- Thanks.

329
00:20:57.770 --> 00:20:59.380
It's funny.

330
00:20:59.427 --> 00:21:00.776
We've only known each other
a short time.

331
00:21:00.819 --> 00:21:04.040
but feels like we've been
friends for years.

332
00:21:04.088 --> 00:21:06.917
You want to tell me
what's going on?

333
00:21:06.966 --> 00:21:09.447
- If this is about the gun...
- Someone could've gotten hurt.

334
00:21:09.493 --> 00:21:11.800
Ty. I was a Navy SEAL for years.

335
00:21:11.847 --> 00:21:12.765
I know what I'm doing.

336
00:21:12.766 --> 00:21:13.767
And I spent years
as a psychiatrist.

337
00:21:13.812 --> 00:21:14.857
I know what I'm doing...
- Okay.

338
00:21:14.904 --> 00:21:16.993
And I can see it in your eyes.

339
00:21:17.041 --> 00:21:19.217
There's something deeper
going on.

340
00:21:19.269 --> 00:21:23.796
To be honest. I noticed it
before Riley disappeared.

341
00:21:23.850 --> 00:21:25.025
Talk to me.

342
00:21:25.076 --> 00:21:27.643
I appreciate your concern.
Ty. I do.

343
00:21:27.693 --> 00:21:28.781
But like I said. I'm good.

344
00:21:32.798 --> 00:21:34.757
It's Paara.

345
00:21:34.806 --> 00:21:36.503
Everyone. they're here.

346
00:21:36.551 --> 00:21:41.121
Paara and her people have
brought us food.

347
00:21:41.179 --> 00:21:43.355
It is so good to see you.
- Hello. Ty.

348
00:21:43.403 --> 00:21:45.274
Thank you so much
for all of this.

349
00:21:45.324 --> 00:21:47.065
All of you. thank you.
We can't thank you enough.

350
00:21:47.113 --> 00:21:48.811
Thank you so much.

351
00:21:48.860 --> 00:21:50.383
How are you feeling?

352
00:21:50.433 --> 00:21:52.261
Well. there are good days
and bad.

353
00:21:52.309 --> 00:21:55.530
Now. today is a great one.

354
00:21:57.503 --> 00:21:58.896
I wish I could stay longer.

355
00:21:58.943 --> 00:22:01.075
but my people are anxious
for us to return with Silas.

356
00:22:03.570 --> 00:22:06.007
Something wrong?

357
00:22:06.058 --> 00:22:07.886
We still need Silas.

358
00:22:07.932 --> 00:22:08.933
Sam is determined to keep him

359
00:22:08.981 --> 00:22:11.244
until he gets his daughter back.

360
00:22:11.295 --> 00:22:13.384
We just need a little more time.

361
00:22:13.434 --> 00:22:16.393
Silas gave us a clue about
where Aldridge might be.

362
00:22:16.446 --> 00:22:18.448
Eve and Levi went to find her.

363
00:22:18.497 --> 00:22:21.239
If they do.
Sam will give Silas back

364
00:22:21.289 --> 00:22:23.378
and everyone will be satisfied.

365
00:22:23.429 --> 00:22:24.648
And if they don't?

366
00:22:26.920 --> 00:22:30.793
I will deliver Silas to you
myself.

367
00:22:30.850 --> 00:22:34.375
Please.
Trust me.

368
00:22:34.428 --> 00:22:37.300
You know that I do.

369
00:22:37.352 --> 00:22:39.049
Thank you.

370
00:22:44.292 --> 00:22:48.078
You know. we don't have to
walk in silence the whole way.

371
00:22:48.133 --> 00:22:50.918
Sorry. I'm just thinking.

372
00:22:50.969 --> 00:22:54.408
You're worried about Josh.
I am too.

373
00:22:56.601 --> 00:22:59.082
But he's not alone.

374
00:22:59.131 --> 00:23:00.437
And neither are you.

375
00:23:02.448 --> 00:23:04.450
You still have me.

376
00:23:05.635 --> 00:23:08.551
Hey. I left you once before.

377
00:23:08.604 --> 00:23:10.040
I won't ever do that again.

378
00:23:12.139 --> 00:23:14.663
Lucas.

379
00:23:19.033 --> 00:23:21.427
Eve. Levi.

380
00:23:29.555 --> 00:23:31.252
She didn't make it.

381
00:23:43.626 --> 00:23:45.541
You know.
whatever you're looking for.

382
00:23:45.602 --> 00:23:47.647
it wasn't back there
the last time you checked.

383
00:23:47.707 --> 00:23:49.143
What's going on?
- Nothing.

384
00:23:49.197 --> 00:23:50.415
I'm just keeping an eye out.

385
00:23:50.471 --> 00:23:51.950
Gavin. you're hiding something.

386
00:23:52.007 --> 00:23:53.791
You don't know me very well.
but I'm pretty observant.

387
00:23:57.538 --> 00:24:00.323
Okay. hey. When I was
hunting that pig earlier.

388
00:24:00.388 --> 00:24:02.041
I came across something.

389
00:24:02.097 --> 00:24:05.535
I didn't want to say it.
I think it's a woolly rhino.

390
00:24:05.609 --> 00:24:08.394
- A what?
- A woolly rhino?

391
00:24:12.147 --> 00:24:13.932
You think
that rhino's following us.

392
00:24:13.992 --> 00:24:17.735
Yes.
We're being hunted.

393
00:24:21.144 --> 00:24:22.450
Come on.

394
00:24:37.765 --> 00:24:39.506
Mom got stabbed.

395
00:24:42.545 --> 00:24:44.112
We tried to get to the light.

396
00:24:44.154 --> 00:24:47.592
but she just lost
too much blood.

397
00:24:51.277 --> 00:24:53.149
I mean. I tried
to get her there. but...

398
00:24:53.189 --> 00:24:56.018
Hey. it's all right.
It's okay.

399
00:25:02.790 --> 00:25:05.750
You've been here since then?

400
00:25:05.789 --> 00:25:06.834
I had to dig a hole deep enough

401
00:25:06.876 --> 00:25:08.616
so the animals
wouldn't get to her.

402
00:25:10.612 --> 00:25:13.311
I just wanted to stay near her.

403
00:25:20.910 --> 00:25:22.738
Please let me go!

404
00:25:22.777 --> 00:25:24.170
Keep moving!

405
00:25:25.341 --> 00:25:26.690
Come on.

406
00:25:28.947 --> 00:25:31.906
Where are you taking me?

407
00:25:31.945 --> 00:25:36.384
- Come on!
- Stop!

408
00:25:36.420 --> 00:25:38.509
No!

409
00:25:38.548 --> 00:25:39.810
Jesus. that's Veronica.

410
00:25:39.852 --> 00:25:41.244
Who the hell are these people?

411
00:25:41.285 --> 00:25:42.677
Look at those machetes.

412
00:25:42.719 --> 00:25:45.983
I don't think they had steel
in 10.000 B.C.

413
00:25:46.022 --> 00:25:48.241
Please let me go!

414
00:25:48.281 --> 00:25:50.109
- We can't leave her with them.
- I agree.

415
00:25:50.149 --> 00:25:52.760
But we don't want to lose
our chance at getting Aldridge.

416
00:25:52.798 --> 00:25:54.931
We better get Veronica fast.

417
00:25:56.970 --> 00:25:59.451
I know we're starving
and lost in time.

418
00:25:59.490 --> 00:26:01.623
but there are
a few bright sides.

419
00:26:01.662 --> 00:26:04.230
- I'm listening.
- No saber tooths.

420
00:26:04.268 --> 00:26:06.183
No wolves that might kill us.

421
00:26:06.224 --> 00:26:08.096
No Fort People chasing us
around all the time.

422
00:26:08.135 --> 00:26:11.182
I mean. eventually. we might
even find a McDonald's.

423
00:26:11.221 --> 00:26:14.442
Ooh. a burger does sound
really good actually.

424
00:26:14.479 --> 00:26:17.308
Right?

425
00:26:17.346 --> 00:26:19.914
- Check it out.
- A house.

426
00:26:19.953 --> 00:26:22.564
They might be able to help us.
- Yeah.

427
00:26:28.035 --> 00:26:30.516
Hello?
- Hello?

428
00:26:30.553 --> 00:26:31.511
Is anyone home?

429
00:26:38.593 --> 00:26:41.291
You know what my parents
used to tell me?

430
00:26:41.328 --> 00:26:44.853
Back in the day. no one
used to lock their doors.

431
00:26:44.892 --> 00:26:46.894
I guess they were wrong.

432
00:26:58.056 --> 00:26:59.971
Wow.
People were way too trusting.

433
00:27:00.011 --> 00:27:01.665
Oh. my God. Food.

434
00:27:12.220 --> 00:27:13.569
- Cold pizza.
- Oh.

435
00:27:15.826 --> 00:27:16.609
Mm.

436
00:27:18.563 --> 00:27:20.826
Let's be quick.
Grab as much as we can.

437
00:27:20.865 --> 00:27:22.997
Get out of here
before they come back.

438
00:27:23.038 --> 00:27:25.257
This is amazing.

439
00:27:31.249 --> 00:27:32.947
Hi. It's Isley and Kieran.

440
00:27:32.986 --> 00:27:34.553
We're in Catalina for the week.

441
00:27:34.594 --> 00:27:37.597
so leave a message and we'll
call you when we get back.

442
00:27:37.636 --> 00:27:39.725
Bye.

443
00:27:41.808 --> 00:27:43.027
You thinking what I'm thinking?

444
00:27:43.068 --> 00:27:44.809
That's a huge answering machine?

445
00:27:44.848 --> 00:27:46.850
No. did you hear what they said?

446
00:27:46.890 --> 00:27:50.198
They won't be back for a week.

447
00:27:50.236 --> 00:27:53.370
We don't have to go anywhere.

448
00:27:53.408 --> 00:27:57.064
Oh. my God.

449
00:27:58.751 --> 00:28:00.143
Come on.
Keep moving.

450
00:28:00.186 --> 00:28:04.103
Where are you taking me?
I haven't done anything.

451
00:28:04.140 --> 00:28:06.316
- Stop dragging.
- Please.

452
00:28:06.356 --> 00:28:07.966
Please just let me go.
I can't...

453
00:28:08.006 --> 00:28:10.138
I can't...

454
00:28:10.178 --> 00:28:11.440
We have to do something.

455
00:28:11.481 --> 00:28:12.482
I know. but we're outnumbered.

456
00:28:12.524 --> 00:28:13.438
It's too risky.

457
00:28:16.175 --> 00:28:18.830
Get up!

458
00:28:18.868 --> 00:28:21.741
- That's it.
- Lucas. what are you doing?

459
00:28:21.777 --> 00:28:23.170
What's it look like?

460
00:28:23.210 --> 00:28:24.777
No.

461
00:28:24.820 --> 00:28:26.952
Come on.
We're running late.

462
00:28:29.294 --> 00:28:30.905
Chris.

463
00:28:39.939 --> 00:28:43.029
Get over there.

464
00:28:43.067 --> 00:28:44.329
Go down.

465
00:28:46.890 --> 00:28:48.674
One of us should go back to
the clearing and ask for help.

466
00:28:48.715 --> 00:28:50.412
The other two can stay here
and keep eyes on Veronica.

467
00:28:53.016 --> 00:28:55.105
You want to stay here.
be my guest.

468
00:28:55.146 --> 00:28:57.888
but I'm not losing anyone else.

469
00:28:57.928 --> 00:28:59.147
Lucas!

470
00:29:07.790 --> 00:29:09.356
Line 'em up over there.
Get 'em ready.

471
00:29:15.869 --> 00:29:17.522
All right. come on.
You two up.

472
00:29:27.774 --> 00:29:31.212
Excuse me.

473
00:29:31.250 --> 00:29:33.949
Can I have some water. please?

474
00:29:33.988 --> 00:29:37.775
- Shut up.
- Please. I'm really thirsty.

475
00:29:42.372 --> 00:29:43.547
Hey!

476
00:29:55.015 --> 00:29:56.886
- Are you okay to walk?
- I think so.

477
00:29:56.927 --> 00:29:58.015
- Okay. get to the woods.
- Come on.

478
00:29:58.058 --> 00:29:59.016
I'll get the key.

479
00:30:01.444 --> 00:30:02.619
Hey!

480
00:30:03.964 --> 00:30:05.096
Got it.

481
00:30:08.222 --> 00:30:10.442
- After them!
- Veronica.

482
00:30:10.483 --> 00:30:12.398
I got the key.
- Oh. thank you.

483
00:30:12.438 --> 00:30:15.006
Go. find them!

484
00:30:15.044 --> 00:30:16.829
Where are they?

485
00:30:18.128 --> 00:30:19.129
This way.

486
00:30:21.126 --> 00:30:23.781
I need to stop.

487
00:30:23.822 --> 00:30:25.084
Oh. no.

488
00:30:29.120 --> 00:30:30.905
Go. go. go.
I got him.

489
00:30:30.945 --> 00:30:33.121
Hey. hey. You can do this.
Come on.

490
00:30:33.161 --> 00:30:35.250
Okay.

491
00:30:36.768 --> 00:30:38.422
- Eve. what are you doing?
- I'm not leaving you.

492
00:30:38.463 --> 00:30:39.987
I promise you. I'll catch up.

493
00:30:40.025 --> 00:30:41.461
Go.
- Be careful.

494
00:30:48.630 --> 00:30:50.936
Go back to where you came
from and nobody gets hurt.

495
00:30:59.925 --> 00:31:01.187
Hey.

496
00:31:18.824 --> 00:31:22.393
Well. Mr. Ginsburg.
I guess it's just you and me.

497
00:31:22.429 --> 00:31:25.650
What do you want to do? Sing?

498
00:31:25.690 --> 00:31:27.082
Play charades?
- Oh. God.

499
00:31:27.123 --> 00:31:28.646
This is literally the best
thing I've ever seen.

500
00:31:28.688 --> 00:31:30.124
I mean. why aren't
there more shows like this?

501
00:31:30.163 --> 00:31:31.687
Why aren't there more shows
about talking puppets

502
00:31:31.727 --> 00:31:33.642
that are supposed to be aliens?

503
00:31:33.683 --> 00:31:34.901
- Yeah. I don't know.
- I mean. come on.

504
00:31:34.943 --> 00:31:36.640
The puppet has its own puppet.
It's genius.

505
00:31:36.682 --> 00:31:38.684
Genius?
You think that's genius?

506
00:31:38.723 --> 00:31:39.855
I mean. all things considered.

507
00:31:39.897 --> 00:31:41.072
it sure as hell beats

508
00:31:41.114 --> 00:31:42.637
sitting in the clearing
eating mushrooms.

509
00:31:49.672 --> 00:31:50.847
What?

510
00:31:53.757 --> 00:31:55.933
Yeah.

511
00:31:55.970 --> 00:31:57.189
Yeah. I guess.

512
00:32:00.793 --> 00:32:04.231
Really?

513
00:32:04.271 --> 00:32:06.578
At least there.
we had our family.

514
00:32:06.615 --> 00:32:09.444
We had hope that
we might one day make it home.

515
00:32:09.483 --> 00:32:10.920
Hey. we'll figure it out.

516
00:32:10.959 --> 00:32:12.874
And I... I don't want
to pretend like

517
00:32:12.916 --> 00:32:15.135
everything's gonna be okay
because we don't know that.

518
00:32:17.434 --> 00:32:20.872
You're right.
Things aren't exactly perfect.

519
00:32:20.909 --> 00:32:23.999
But...

520
00:32:24.038 --> 00:32:25.518
I don't know.

521
00:32:25.559 --> 00:32:26.690
There's a million reasons
to be freaking out right now.

522
00:32:28.209 --> 00:32:32.866
And for some reason.
being here with you. I'm not.

523
00:32:32.901 --> 00:32:34.380
- Josh.
- What?

524
00:32:34.421 --> 00:32:36.684
Are you gonna pretend like
you don't care about me too?

525
00:32:36.725 --> 00:32:38.770
I don't know how I'm feeling.

526
00:32:38.810 --> 00:32:43.162
We were thrown into
the craziest situation.

527
00:32:43.198 --> 00:32:45.679
That doesn't make us a couple.

528
00:32:45.717 --> 00:32:47.980
And it doesn't make me
any less scared.

529
00:32:50.628 --> 00:32:53.326
Okay. so what do you want to do?

530
00:32:55.276 --> 00:32:58.802
Maybe we should just
get out of here

531
00:32:58.838 --> 00:33:01.319
and then figure it out.

532
00:33:01.358 --> 00:33:02.446
Great. Yeah.

533
00:33:02.488 --> 00:33:05.143
I'll go see
if I can find some cash.

534
00:33:15.435 --> 00:33:16.741
It's still out there.

535
00:33:16.783 --> 00:33:18.175
We just have
to keep moving. okay?

536
00:33:18.217 --> 00:33:20.915
Just stay ahead of it.

537
00:33:20.954 --> 00:33:23.130
Shh.

538
00:33:23.168 --> 00:33:25.562
Shh.

539
00:33:25.602 --> 00:33:26.994
Get behind me. get behind me.

540
00:33:52.843 --> 00:33:53.931
It's so cute.

541
00:33:58.579 --> 00:34:00.276
Iz.

542
00:34:00.315 --> 00:34:03.318
Shh.
It's okay.

543
00:34:03.358 --> 00:34:05.273
It's all right.

544
00:34:05.312 --> 00:34:08.054
It's okay.
Shh.

545
00:34:12.306 --> 00:34:16.354
I think it wants to be friends.

546
00:34:16.390 --> 00:34:18.262
It's amazing.

547
00:34:24.081 --> 00:34:26.779
Let's go.

548
00:34:36.941 --> 00:34:38.116
Oh. no.

549
00:34:41.982 --> 00:34:43.897
We should hide.

550
00:34:43.937 --> 00:34:47.245
We're too exposed.
There's nowhere to go.

551
00:34:47.282 --> 00:34:50.677
And that rhino's coming for us.

552
00:34:50.714 --> 00:34:53.020
So what do we do?

553
00:34:53.060 --> 00:34:56.759
We have to cross that field.

554
00:34:56.797 --> 00:34:58.712
If we cross the field.
they'll see us.

555
00:34:58.752 --> 00:35:01.494
Then we're sitting ducks.

556
00:35:01.534 --> 00:35:05.494
Actually.
I don't think they can see us.

557
00:35:05.529 --> 00:35:07.444
So woolly rhinos
are practically blind.

558
00:35:07.484 --> 00:35:10.226
They use sound to guide them.

559
00:35:10.265 --> 00:35:11.702
I can draw their attention
away from us.

560
00:35:11.744 --> 00:35:14.704
buy us enough time
to get across the field.

561
00:35:14.740 --> 00:35:16.786
Go.

562
00:35:45.066 --> 00:35:47.242
My leg!

563
00:35:49.499 --> 00:35:51.501
Shh. shh.

564
00:35:56.493 --> 00:35:57.668
Dad!

565
00:36:01.013 --> 00:36:02.188
We need to move.

566
00:36:02.229 --> 00:36:04.580
It's my leg.
I can't run.

567
00:36:15.131 --> 00:36:16.524
Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.

568
00:36:20.257 --> 00:36:22.433
Get down!

569
00:36:22.474 --> 00:36:23.431
Stay down.

570
00:36:31.641 --> 00:36:32.946
See?

571
00:36:36.855 --> 00:36:38.422
Let's go.
- Let's get out of here!

572
00:36:38.464 --> 00:36:39.856
- Come on!
- I'm trying.

573
00:36:42.546 --> 00:36:44.722
Are you stealing money
from some kid's piggy bank?

574
00:36:44.762 --> 00:36:47.069
It's not like
they take Venmo here.

575
00:36:49.064 --> 00:36:53.460
Besides. I'm leaving behind
a pretty good present.

576
00:36:53.497 --> 00:36:57.327
- Buy Apple stock. Nice.
- Right?

577
00:36:59.578 --> 00:37:01.537
All right. I think we're gonna

578
00:37:01.576 --> 00:37:02.969
get. like. 100 bucks
out of this.

579
00:37:03.010 --> 00:37:05.883
It doesn't sound like much.
but it's 1988.

580
00:37:05.922 --> 00:37:07.837
I'm pretty sure
everything's cheaper here.

581
00:37:07.875 --> 00:37:09.442
All right.
Want to get out of here?

582
00:37:09.483 --> 00:37:10.571
Hang on a second. Josh.

583
00:37:10.614 --> 00:37:13.225
It's cool.
No need for a talk.

584
00:37:13.264 --> 00:37:16.398
I'm sorry. okay?

585
00:37:16.436 --> 00:37:18.133
It's just this
whole thing feels like

586
00:37:18.174 --> 00:37:20.960
this really bad nightmare
that I can't wake up from.

587
00:37:20.996 --> 00:37:22.694
And I'm afraid that when I do.

588
00:37:22.734 --> 00:37:26.695
the newspapers are
still gonna say 1988.

589
00:37:26.732 --> 00:37:29.735
- Oh. you got to be kidding me.
- What?

590
00:37:36.464 --> 00:37:38.553
I don't understand.

591
00:37:38.593 --> 00:37:40.856
A sinkhole never opened up
at the Hollywood sign in 1988.

592
00:37:40.896 --> 00:37:42.376
No. it didn't.

593
00:37:42.417 --> 00:37:44.288
So why is now?

594
00:37:44.329 --> 00:37:45.982
I don't know.

595
00:37:46.022 --> 00:37:49.504
but if this sinkhole's anything
like the one in La Brea.

596
00:37:49.541 --> 00:37:53.371
we may have found
our back to 10.000 B.C.

597
00:38:00.055 --> 00:38:02.754
- Where the hell are they?
- I don't know.

598
00:38:04.401 --> 00:38:05.576
We should go back and find them.

599
00:38:05.617 --> 00:38:09.317
No.
No. we stay right here.

600
00:38:09.354 --> 00:38:10.877
They'll find us.

601
00:38:15.654 --> 00:38:16.698
What happened?

602
00:38:16.739 --> 00:38:18.828
I took care of him.
We're good.

603
00:38:18.868 --> 00:38:21.349
Where's Eve?

604
00:38:21.389 --> 00:38:22.694
What do you mean.
"Where's Eve?"

605
00:38:22.734 --> 00:38:23.735
She was with you.

606
00:38:26.471 --> 00:38:29.256
- Pull!
- Hyah!

607
00:38:53.365 --> 00:38:56.411
We're here.

608
00:38:56.450 --> 00:38:57.712
What do you mean?

609
00:38:57.753 --> 00:39:00.974
But the building's
all the way over there.

610
00:39:01.011 --> 00:39:02.230
Allow me.

611
00:39:22.215 --> 00:39:25.349
I did not see that coming.

612
00:39:25.384 --> 00:39:28.300
This is our way
into the building.

613
00:39:30.642 --> 00:39:32.427
In Dagobah.
Luke went into a cave

614
00:39:32.467 --> 00:39:33.947
and came face-to-face
with Vader.

615
00:39:33.987 --> 00:39:35.902
It was super terrifying.

616
00:39:35.944 --> 00:39:38.251
Is this gonna be like that?

617
00:39:38.288 --> 00:39:40.290
Probably.

618
00:39:46.329 --> 00:39:47.808
- Okay.
- Yeah.

619
00:39:47.848 --> 00:39:48.805
We're nearly there.

620
00:39:48.849 --> 00:39:50.590
Thank God!
Are you guys okay?

621
00:39:50.627 --> 00:39:53.064
- Ty. help!
- Give 'em a hand!

622
00:39:53.104 --> 00:39:54.410
- What happened?
- Grab her leg.

623
00:39:54.451 --> 00:39:55.539
- It's fine. We're fine.
- Be careful. be careful.

624
00:39:55.581 --> 00:39:57.931
- We're fine.
- Easy. easy.

625
00:40:00.143 --> 00:40:01.841
Where's Eve and Levi?

626
00:40:01.881 --> 00:40:03.840
- Eve was taken.
- By who?

627
00:40:03.879 --> 00:40:06.273
I... I don't know.
I don't know who they were.

628
00:40:09.572 --> 00:40:12.270
You all right?
- Yeah.

629
00:40:12.309 --> 00:40:14.267
What about Levi?

630
00:40:22.822 --> 00:40:24.476
Whoa.

631
00:40:24.517 --> 00:40:26.432
Halt!

632
00:40:26.472 --> 00:40:28.909
Hold up!

633
00:40:28.946 --> 00:40:31.079
Get in there!

634
00:40:31.120 --> 00:40:32.252
Levi.

635
00:40:35.117 --> 00:40:36.815
Hey.
You all right?

636
00:40:36.856 --> 00:40:39.032
I thought you got away.

637
00:40:39.072 --> 00:40:40.639
I did.

638
00:40:40.678 --> 00:40:42.463
I came back. gave myself up.

639
00:40:42.503 --> 00:40:44.418
Why?

640
00:40:44.459 --> 00:40:46.287
Told you I wasn't leaving you.

641
00:40:52.583 --> 00:40:54.063
This should help for the moment.

642
00:40:59.491 --> 00:41:02.146
How does that feel?
- Better.

643
00:41:02.186 --> 00:41:03.622
Yeah. Do you think you can
walk on your own?

644
00:41:03.663 --> 00:41:04.795
Yeah.

645
00:41:11.005 --> 00:41:12.224
Dad.

646
00:41:15.915 --> 00:41:18.918
Is that the Hollywood sign?

647
00:41:18.955 --> 00:41:20.957
No. it can't be.

648
00:41:26.256 --> 00:41:27.344
No. no. no.
It's not possible.

649
00:41:27.385 --> 00:41:28.995
We jumped through
a sinkhole in Seattle.

650
00:41:29.035 --> 00:41:30.732
It's nowhere near Los Angeles.

651
00:41:39.071 --> 00:41:40.029
Oh. my God.

652
00:41:44.371 --> 00:41:46.330
I've seen that building
back home.

653
00:41:46.370 --> 00:41:48.372
I can't believe it.

654
00:41:48.413 --> 00:41:51.894
That sinkhole brought us to LA.
